COPY ~TIMaeth/spells/SPPR515.spl~ ~override~
SAY NAME1 ~Undead Ward~ // unidentified name for items OR spell name
SAY NAME2 ~Identified Name~ // identified name for items; not used for spells
SAY UNIDENTIFIED_DESC ~When an undead creature attempts to enter the protected area, the creature is affected by the ward as if it were being turned by a priest the same level as the caster (up to level 20).  The casting Priest need not have the ability to turn undead himself. The results of the turning attempt are calculated normally.  If a large number of undead assult the warded area, not all of them are turned by the spell, since normal limitations apply.  Undead who are unaffected by the turning attempt ignore the undead ward for its duration.~ // unidentified description for items, spell description for spells
